The paper deals with the computational complexity of truthful mechanisms for combinatorial auctions, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of game theory (cs.GT), data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational complexity (cs.CC), and electronic commerce (cs.EC). The paper presents computational hardness results for various classes of succinctly described valuations, which involves analyzing the complexity of designing truthful mechanisms for combinatorial auctions. Therefore, it is likely to be relevant to these sub-categories.
